Tribunos were first appointed in 494 B.c., after the first secession to the Sacred Mount. At first there were but two, afterwards the number was increased to five, and finally to ten. They were origi· nally appointed to afford protec- tion to the common people; and that they might be able to aflord such protection, their persons were declared sacred and iuvio- lable. They gradually acquired tl1e right of vetoing any act which a magistrate might under· take during his term of office.
